👉 the banner image is being <strong data-start="86" data-end="114">cropped too aggressively</strong>, especially vertically.<br data-start="138" data-end="141">
That’s because of <code data-start="159" data-end="178">object-fit: cover</code> + wrong positioning + too small height.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="nkwvgb" data-start="220" data-end="254">Fix strategy (quick + correct)</h3>
<ul data-start="255" data-end="426">
<li data-section-id="19m9wqp" data-start="255" data-end="295">
<p data-start="257" data-end="295">Keep <code data-start="262" data-end="269">cover</code> (so it still looks clean)</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1h20kll" data-start="296" data-end="357">
<p data-start="298" data-end="357">BUT show the important part → <code data-start="328" data-end="357">object-position: center top</code></p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="zrzf4p" data-start="358" data-end="405">
<p data-start="360" data-end="405">Slightly increase height so it’s not squeezed</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="ayzfl7" data-start="406" data-end="426">
<p data-start="408" data-end="426">Make it responsive</p>
</li>
</ul>
