<ul data-start="32" data-end="139">
<li data-section-id="uzbxou" data-start="32" data-end="59">
<p data-start="34" data-end="59"><code data-start="34" data-end="41">cover</code> = crops image ❌</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="t1kzy9" data-start="60" data-end="139">
<p data-start="62" data-end="139"><code data-start="62" data-end="71">contain</code> = shows full image but can look too big/small depending on height</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="141" data-end="232">So the fix is:<br data-start="155" data-end="158">
👉 <strong data-start="161" data-end="232">medium banner height + <code data-start="186" data-end="207">object-fit: contain</code> + centered positioning</strong></p>
<p data-start="234" data-end="320">I’ve balanced it so the banner is <strong data-start="268" data-end="319">not huge, not cropped, fully visible, and clean</strong>.</p>
